07/04/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Robert Deutsch, a senior US adviser on Iraq, praised Macedonia's commitment to the international partnership in support of Iraq's political and economic development goals. He met with ranking officials from the defence ministry and foreign affairs ministry on Thursday (6 April), as well as with members of the army's special operations unit. Deutsch stressed the vital role that international forces in Iraq will continue to play in helping the country's security forces assume responsibility in the coming year.
In other news, Turkish Transport Minister Binali Yildirim was due to visit Macedonia on Friday. Talks will focus on investment possibilities and regional initiatives, such as Corridor 8. (Makfax, MIA - 07/04/06; Makfax - 06/04/06)
